  {user_id: 1, title: "Tutorials", body: "Travis CI - Part 1 Basic Setup - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g0KsiCj3CgQ&t=272s\r\n\r\nTravis CI Tutorial - How to Use Travis CI with Github for Continuous Integration - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Uft5KBimzyk\r\n\r\n006: Setup User Authentication with Devise - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zJYuLebl-Js\r\n\r\nUser And Admin Accounts With Devise | Authentication Ruby On Rails 5.2 Tutorial - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7v2EMmfBJL8\r\n\r\nFast Ruby on Rails 5 Bootstrap Tutorial - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ryelNMlp-iY\r\n\r\n**\r\nRuby on Rails 5 Absolute Beginner Tutorial | Intro To Scaffold Crud - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tVVQLMKCpj0\r\n\r\n", category_id: 6},
  {user_id: 1, title: "Add field to table", body: "- rails generate migration add_name_of_migration\r\nThis will generate a migrate file, in there add the following lines before migrating:\r\n\r\n- add_column :table_name, :field_name :field_type (ex: add_column :users, :user_name :string\r\n- add_index :table_name, :field_name, unique: true (if the field needs to be unique)\r\n\r\nthen run:\r\n- rails db:migrate.\r\n", category_id: 6},
