  {user_id: 1, title: "Paper clip", body: "- brew install imagemagick\r\n- visit: https://rubygems.org/gems/paperclip\r\n- add gem to Gemfile\r\n- run bundle install\r\n- in post model add:\r\n  -   # For paperclip to handle images\r\n  - has_attached_file :image, styles: { large: \"600x600>\", medium: \"300x300>\", thumb: \"100x100#\" }\r\n  - validates_attachment_content_type :image, content_type: /\\Aimage\\/.*\\z/\r\n- rails generate paperclip post image\r\n- rails db:migrate\r\n- Fix the form tag as such:\r\n  - <%= form_for @post, url: posts_path, html: { multipart: true } do |form| %>\r\n        - I needed to delete the url:posts_path to be able to edit the post, and I can still save new posts!\r\n- Fix the views in the form as such:\r\n  - <%= form.file_field :image %>\r\n- In the posts controller add :image to the params permitted as such:\r\n  - params.require(:post).permit(:message, :user_id, :image)\r\n- Add the image to the views as such:\r\n  - <%= image_tag @post.image.url(:medium) %> (or (:large), according to which page it will be displayed in)", category_id: 6},
